{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f7246df4-bb32-4ffe-bd04-5997926e9f35","content":"Your project is already configured for Microsoft Testing Platform (via `global.json`). You can use the built-in hot reload support:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis watches for file changes and automatically re-runs affected tests. It's ideal for rapid iteration since it avoids a full rebuild cycle each time.\n\n**About the failing test:** `RemoveStock` never throws — it just subtracts without validation. You'll need to add a guard like:\n\n```csharp\npublic void RemoveStock(string sku, int quantity)\n{\n    var current = _stock.GetValueOrDefault(sku);\n    if (quantity > current)\n        throw new InvalidOperationException(\"Insufficient stock\");\n    _stock[sku] = current - quantity;\n}\n```\n\nStart the hot reload watcher, make the fix, and it will re-run automatically.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0da4f981-003e-4f5b-8594-216fb5fabfdb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up hot reload for their test project. Since this is a .NET project using Microsoft Testing Platform (as indicated by the `global.json` `test.runner` setting), they can use `dotnet test --hotreload` or `dotnet watch test`.\n\nLet me check what's available. With .NET 10 and Microsoft Testing Platform, the recommended approach is `dotnet test --hotreload` which watches for file changes and re-runs tests automatically.\n\nActually, looking at this more carefully - with .NET 10 and the Microsoft Testing Platform runner, there's `dotnet test --hotreload` support. But let me also consider `dotnet watch test` which is the more traditional approach.\n\n\nFor .NET 10 with Microsoft Testing Platform, `dotnet test --hotreload` is the way to go since the project is configured to use that runner. This command automatically watches for changes and reruns the affected tests, which is perfect for their workflow.\n\nI should also point out that there's a bug in their RemoveStock method—it doesn't actually throw an exception when trying to remove more stock than is available, which is what the test is checking for.","outputTokens":581,"requestId":"0830:1DCDBF:7F263E7:8DB920D:69EAC87C"},"id":"04d0eff2-03c7-4758-b446-b4b96798ab83","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:34:01.495Z","parentId":"e4fd7537-2059-4cc1-b812-0ff28602a98e"}
